# DCP User Roles

## Overview

DCP role-based access control (RBAC) model defines permissions for every user in the platform.

---

# 1. Super Admin

## Permissions

- Manage entire platform
- Create organizations
- Delete organizations
- View all logs
- Manage licenses
- System configuration
- Global security settings

---

# 2. Organization Admin

## Permissions

- Manage organization
- Invite users
- Remove users
- Create departments
- Create groups
- Assign moderators
- View organization analytics

---

# 3. Moderator

## Permissions

- Manage channels
- Manage groups
- Remove inappropriate messages
- Manage members
- Report security issues

---

# 4. Employee (User)

## Permissions

- Send messages
- Create chats
- Join groups
- Share files
- Use AI Assistant
- Make voice calls
- Make video calls

---

# 5. Guest

## Permissions

- Limited access
- Read-only channels
- Temporary invitations
- No administration rights

---

## Security Principle

Every role only receives the permissions required for its responsibilities.
